==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[apologize]]

===Etymology===
Compare with French ''[[apologiser]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* ''US:'' {{IPA|/Гүв„ўГӢЛҶpГүвҖҳl.Гүв„ў.ГҠВӨaГүВӘz/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|apologis|ing}}

# {{intransitive}} To make an [[apology]] or [[defence]].
# {{intransitive}} To make an apology or [[excuse]]; to make [[acknowledgment]] of some [[fault]] or [[offense]], with expression of [[regret]] for it, by way of [[amends]];&mdash;with for; as, my correspondent apologized for not answering my letter.
# {{intransitive}} To express regret that an event has occurred.

